TITLE: Setting Up Initial Data for Chart.js Line Chart in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet sets up the initial data for the line chart. It defines constants for data count and number configuration, creates labels using utility functions, and sets up two datasets with random data and color configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/master/docs/samples/line/line.md#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const DATA_COUNT = 7;
const NUMBER_CFG = {count: DATA_COUNT, min: -100, max: 100};

const labels = Utils.months({count: 7});
const data = {
  labels: labels,
  datasets: [
    {
      label: 'Dataset 1',
      data: Utils.numbers(NUMBER_CFG),
      borderColor: Utils.CHART_COLORS.red,
      backgroundColor: Utils.transparentize(Utils.CHART_COLORS.red, 0.5),
    },
    {
      label: 'Dataset 2',
      data: Utils.numbers(NUMBER_CFG),
      borderColor: Utils.CHART_COLORS.blue,
      backgroundColor: Utils.transparentize(Utils.CHART_COLORS.blue, 0.5),
    }
  ]
};
```

