TITLE: Creating Dual Y-Axes Chart in Chart.js
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a chart with two Y axes in Chart.js. The datasets are mapped to their respective axes using the yAxisID property, with one axis positioned on the left and the other on the right.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/master/docs/axes/cartesian/index.md#2025-04-08_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const myChart = new Chart(ctx, {
    type: 'line',
    data: {
        datasets: [{
            data: [20, 50, 100, 75, 25, 0],
            label: 'Left dataset',

            // This binds the dataset to the left y axis
            yAxisID: 'left-y-axis'
        }, {
            data: [0.1, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 1.5, 0],
            label: 'Right dataset',

            // This binds the dataset to the right y axis
            yAxisID: 'right-y-axis'
        }],
        labels: ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun']
    },
    options: {
        scales: {
            'left-y-axis': {
                type: 'linear',
                position: 'left'
            },
            'right-y-axis': {
                type: 'linear',
                position: 'right'
            }
        }
    }
});
```

