TITLE: Implementing Label Callback for Currency Formatting in Chart.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use a label callback to format tooltip values as USD currency. It uses the Intl.NumberFormat API to apply proper formatting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/master/docs/configuration/tooltip.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const chart = new Chart(ctx, {
    type: 'line',
    data: data,
    options: {
        plugins: {
            tooltip: {
                callbacks: {
                    label: function(context) {
                        let label = context.dataset.label || '';

                        if (label) {
                            label += ': ';
                        }
                        if (context.parsed.y !== null) {
                            label += new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' }).format(context.parsed.y);
                        }
                        return label;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
});
```

