TITLE: Triggering Tooltip Display in Chart.js
DESCRIPTION: This function toggles the tooltip display on chart elements. It either hides the tooltip by clearing active elements, or shows the tooltip at the center of the chart area by setting specific elements (third elements of datasets 0 and 1) as active.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/master/docs/samples/advanced/programmatic-events.md#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function triggerTooltip(chart) {
  const tooltip = chart.tooltip;
  if (tooltip.getActiveElements().length > 0) {
    tooltip.setActiveElements([], {x: 0, y: 0});
  } else {
    const chartArea = chart.chartArea;
    tooltip.setActiveElements([
      {
        datasetIndex: 0,
        index: 2,
      }, {
        datasetIndex: 1,
        index: 2,
      }
    ],
    {
      x: (chartArea.left + chartArea.right) / 2,
      y: (chartArea.top + chartArea.bottom) / 2,
    });
  }

  chart.update();
}
```

